<br>
it is my belief that spell hit damage should be made known in the same fashion melee hits are. <br>
<br>
the unwarrented &quot;useless&quot; offensive caster image and pro-melee bias groups often have when seeking group members is partly to blame because of this. to keep this poll as unbiased as possible, here are a few supportive opinions to aid you in your choice:<br>
<br>
-players are unlikely to invite a caster in a pickup group who may turn out to be an xp sponge. if only spell damage was hearable as melee hits are, this would no longer be a valid fear.<br>
<br>
-players see a constant stream of numbers from that powerful looking iksar monk, meanwhile, the frail high elf wizard/mage is seemingly just sitting there, getting up only once in the battle to cast... as if he's doing nothing. <br>
while experianced players may understand that 1 cast may equal a 1890 damage rain, none the less, this imagry leaves a subconscious mental imprint on all players regardless of skill, biasing their choices when looking for potential group mates in the future. if players could only see that 1 cast resulted in 1/4 of the creatures hp being shaved off, they probably would be less inclined to turn away a wizard or mage for a group.<br>
<br>
-spell hit damage remaining unknown is partly to blame why we are so rarely given upgrades/modifications to our spells. we and what we can do are a mystery to much of the player base. it is my belief, if what we were capable of was public, verant would be forced to give us attention where attention is due, since our problems would now be common knowledge.<br>
<br>
-all players understand the value of continuous damage. however, few understand why fast damage is valuable. <br>
by making spell hits known just as melee hits are, players would understand why things die quicker when there is a wizard or mage in your group, allowing the group to pull more over all. this would inspire players to seek out inviting a caster when forming groups in the future.<br>
<br>
-most people already think offensive casters are the least useful type of classes. so, what harm does it do to let players know our damage then? the worst thing that could happen is we live up to that stereotype they already have. but then again, they may find out we arent as useless as they thought. in fact, they may find out we are a valuable asset to a situation.<br>
<br>
-increased spam wouldnt be a problem. like melee hits, the default would be &quot;others spell damage on&quot;, which you could turn off any time via the chat filter if you are not interested in hearing it. <br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
<br>
to keep this poll as unbiased as possible, here are a few opposing opinions to aid you in your choice:<br>
<br>
-even though most of the time casters get full hits, however, people always remember the bad over the good. when players see us getting partial resists, it will only further influence the &quot;useless caster&quot; image.<br>
<br>
-players already think we are the least useful classes. doing this will only cause everyone else to be even more aware, making finding a group more difficult. <br>
<br>
-lower level casters often get partial resists. if other players knew this, grouping would be very hard for wizards and mages levels 1-30.<br>
<br>
-i dont see the point in adding any more spam which serves no purpose.<br>
<br>
